PERTH (miningweekly.com) – Mining services provider SRG Global has been awarded a A$95-million civil infrastructure maintenance term contract with aluminium major Alcoa. The services will be provided at Alcoa’s Kwinana alumina refinery in Western Australia with a contract duration of five years comprising an initial three-year term plus a two-year option. The scope of work includes civil maintenance services including minor civil works, bauxite residue management and bulk materials handling services at the Kwinana bauxite residue storage, refinery and port facilities. SRG said on Wednesday that the contract provides panel membership for the potential provision of civil services work across Alcoa’s mining and refining, including port, sites in Western Australia. “We are very pleased to have secured a new five-year contract with Alcoa’s Kwinana refinery. This is a significant contract award for SRG Global and demonstrates the value of the WBHO Infrastructure acquisition that is now successfully integrated into SRG Global,” SRG Global MD David Macgeorge said. “This contract continues a 35-year history on this site and we look forward to continuing to deliver value-engineered services to Alcoa. The contract will support over 100 local jobs and extends our ongoing commitment to the development and employment of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander throughout the duration of the contract.”